{"questionId":"9073486","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A beam of monochromatic light from infinity is incident on a converging lens A. The diagram shows three wavefronts of the light and the focal point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> of the lens.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/ffdb48d82d39dd0ea7f72c3aefb6feb57c234a14.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Lens A has a focal length of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>00</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math>. An object is placed <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>50</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cm</mi></math> to the left of A. Show by calculation that a screen should be placed about <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math> from A to display a focused image.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>v</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>00</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>50</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;✓</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>36</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>«</mo><mi>cm</mi><mo>»</mo></math>&nbsp;✓</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9073486","referenceCode":"20N.3.SL.TZ0.11b","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Lens A has a focal length of 4.00 cm. An object is placed 4.50 cm to the left of A. Show by calculation that a screen should be placed about 0.4 m from A to display a focused image","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging","Option C: Imaging (Core topics)","C